claim.claim-text:
1. A method of creating a semiconductor structure comprising:
providing an insulator layer on a substrate;
patterning said insulator layer to form at least one recess in said insulator layer;
forming at least one conductive strap within said at least one recess in said insulator layer;
patterning a plurality of fins above said insulator layer, relative to a bottom of said semiconductor structure, each of said fins comprising a central semiconductor portion and conductive end portions, said at least one conductive strap being positioned within said insulator layer below said plurality of fins, relative to said bottom of said semiconductor structure, said plurality of fins being parallel to each other, and said at least one conductive strap being perpendicular to said fins and contacting said fins, and said at least one conductive strap comprising projected portions extending into said fins, collinear with each of said plurality of fins, relative to said bottom of said semiconductor structure;
forming a gate dielectric contacting and covering said central semiconductor portion of said plurality of fins; and
forming a gate conductor contacting and covering said gate dielectric,
said at least one conductive strap being disposed in at least one of a source region and a drain region of said semiconductor structure.

6. A method of creating a semiconductor structure comprising:
providing an insulator layer on a substrate;
patterning said insulator layer to form at least one recess in said insulator layer;
forming at least one conductive strap within said at least one recess in said insulator layer;
patterning a plurality of fins above said insulator layer, relative to a bottom of said semiconductor structure, each of said fins comprising a central semiconductor portion and conductive end portions,
said at least one conductive strap being positioned within said insulator layer below said fins, relative to said bottom of said semiconductor structure,
said plurality of fins being parallel to each other and said at least one conductive strap being perpendicular to said fins and contacting said fins, and
said at least one conductive strap comprising projected portions extending into said fins, collinear with each of said plurality of fins, relative to said bottom of said semiconductor structure;

forming a gate dielectric contacting and covering said central semiconductor portion of said plurality of fins; and
forming a gate conductor contacting and covering said gate dielectric,
said at least one conductive strap electrically contacting and connecting said fins,
said at least one conductive strap producing a physical strain within said central semiconductor portion of said plurality of fins, and
said at least one conductive strap being disposed in at least one of a source region and a drain region of said semiconductor structure.

11. A method comprising:
providing a silicon-on-insulator (SOI) structure comprising a silicon layer formed on an insulator layer formed on a buried oxide substrate;
patterning said SOI structure to form at least one recess through said silicon layer and at least partially into said insulator layer;
forming a conductive strap within said at least one recess;
patterning a plurality of fins above said SOI structure, relative to a bottom of said SOI structure, each of said fins comprising a central semiconductor portion and conductive end portions,
said conductive strap being positioned within said insulator layer below said plurality of fins, relative to said bottom of said SOI structure,
said plurality of fins being parallel to each other, and said conductive strap being perpendicular to said fins and contacting said fins, and
said conductive strap comprising projected portions extending into said fins, collinear with each of said plurality of fins, relative to said bottom of said SOI structure;

forming a gate dielectric on at least a portion of said plurality of fins, said gate dielectric contacting and covering said central semiconductor portion of said plurality of fins; and
forming a gate conductor on said gate dielectric, said gate conductor contacting and covering said gate dielectric,
said conductive strap being disposed in at least one of a source region and a drain region of said SOI structure.

16. A method comprising:
providing a silicon-on-insulator (SOI) structure comprising a silicon layer formed on an insulator layer formed on a buried oxide substrate;
patterning said SOI structure to form at least one recess through said silicon layer and at least partially into said insulator layer;
forming a conductive strap within said at least one recess;
patterning a plurality of fins above said SOI structure, relative to a bottom of said SOI structure, each of said fins comprising a central semiconductor portion and conductive end portions,
said conductive strap being positioned within said insulator layer below said plurality of fins, relative to said bottom of said SOI structure,
said plurality of fins being parallel to each other, and said conductive strap being perpendicular to said fins and contacting said fins, and
said conductive strap comprising projected portions extending into said fins, collinear with each of said plurality of fins, relative to said bottom of said SOI structure;

forming a gate dielectric on at least a portion of said plurality of fins, said gate dielectric contacting and covering said central semiconductor portion of said plurality of fins; and
forming a gate conductor on said gate dielectric, said gate conductor contacting and covering said gate dielectric,
said conductive strap electrically contacting and connecting said fins,
said conductive strap producing a physical strain within said central semiconductor portion of said plurality of fins, and
said conductive strap being disposed in at least one of a source region and a drain region of said SOI structure.
